Hey, Benny. Come on!

1362
01:44:45,557 --> 01:44:47,182
(knocking)

1363
01:44:49,019 --> 01:44:50,643
(knocking)

1364
01:44:53,981 --> 01:44:55,606
(knocking)

1365
01:45:14,460 --> 01:45:16,832
- You look swell, kid.
- Likewise.

1366
01:45:16,963 --> 01:45:19,002
Just swell.

1367
01:45:28,516 --> 01:45:31,185
- Sorry about last night.
- Forget it.

1368
01:45:35,773 --> 01:45:39,771
- If I'd known I'd run into you, I'd have...
- Oh, that's OK.

1369
01:45:51,455 --> 01:45:53,946
- What the hell's the big idea?
- Elmer, honey...

1370
01:45:54,083 --> 01:45:58,330
- You think I'll sit still for a shakedown?
- How could I put the squeeze on you?

1371
01:45:58,462 --> 01:46:02,543
- Who'll take the word of a hooker?
- The old badger game, huh?

1372
01:46:02,675 --> 01:46:05,676
- I only wanted to see you for...
- For what?

1373
01:46:05,803 --> 01:46:08,045
- Well, for...
- For what?

1374
01:46:09,181 --> 01:46:14,805
Gee, honey, look. Look, I'm almost
packed. The cops gave me notice.

1375
01:46:14,937 --> 01:46:17,607
I got a ticket on the midnight bus.

1376
01:46:30,911 --> 01:46:33,151
I got no beef against you.

1377
01:46:34,288 --> 01:46:37,242
I only wanted to see you once more,

1378
01:46:37,374 --> 01:46:41,502
kick around some old memories,
maybe have a few laughs.

1379
01:46:41,629 --> 01:46:43,668
Go on.

1380
01:46:48,594 --> 01:46:50,800
Who am I kiddin'?

1381
01:46:52,222 --> 01:46:56,719
When you first hit town, I figured
you could go to hell without my help.

1382
01:46:56,852 --> 01:47:00,720
When you came bustin' in last night
like God Almighty wearin' a tin star,

1383
01:47:00,856 --> 01:47:06,017
I got mad, boilin' mad. All I could think of
was how you took me and ditched me.

1384
01:47:06,153 --> 01:47:09,902
That's all I could think of.
Me, little Miss Lulu, the dumb pushover.

1385
01:47:10,032 --> 01:47:12,784
And when the cops said
"Get out of town in 24 hours",

1386
01:47:12,910 --> 01:47:15,235
all I wanted to do was spit in your eye,

1387
01:47:15,371 --> 01:47:18,905
blackmail you, a shakedown -
anything to hurt you.

1388
01:47:21,460 --> 01:47:23,085
But...

1389
01:47:24,713 --> 01:47:27,383
But when you walked in just now...

1390
01:47:29,635 --> 01:47:32,090
Gee, honey...

1391
01:47:32,221 --> 01:47:35,720
it was like the first time
between us all over again.

1392
01:47:37,309 --> 01:47:39,765
All goose pimples and...

1393
01:47:44,441 --> 01:47:46,564
You'd better beat it.

1394
01:47:48,612 --> 01:47:50,854
I'm sorry I phoned.

1395
01:47:51,865 --> 01:47:55,032
I won't make any trouble.
Not even if I could.

1396
01:47:58,581 --> 01:48:00,822
Please go now.

1397
01:48:04,961 --> 01:48:08,377
I did run out on you
back there in Kansas, didn't I?

1398
01:48:09,674 --> 01:48:13,375
It's nobody's fault.
Except maybe my old man's.

1399
01:48:13,511 --> 01:48:16,263
- Ever hear from him?
- Once, last Christmas.

1400
01:48:16,389 --> 01:48:21,728
The letter said "Daughter, read
1st Kings, Chapter 21, Verse 23. "

1401
01:48:21,853 --> 01:48:27,096
I looked it up. It said "And the dogs
in the street shall eat Jezebel. "

1402
01:48:28,943 --> 01:48:31,315
My old man and his Bible.

1403
01:48:32,947 --> 01:48:34,987
Tell me...

1404
01:48:35,825 --> 01:48:39,241
how is it some people can
only find hate in the Bible?

1405
01:48:43,750 --> 01:48:48,459
- Where will you be going to?
- I think I'll go tramping through Paris.

1406
01:48:48,588 --> 01:48:51,672
Can you use some cash?
Sort of tide you over?

1407
01:48:56,804 --> 01:48:59,556
Just... just kiss me goodbye.

1408
01:49:00,892 --> 01:49:02,766
Just once.

1409
01:49:46,310 --> 01:49:48,350
What's she doin'?

1410
01:49:58,531 --> 01:50:00,570
Stay awhile.

1411
01:50:02,743 --> 01:50:04,783
Talk to me.

1412
01:50:06,122 --> 01:50:08,909
Oh, don't go yet. Please don't go.

1413
01:50:11,669 --> 01:50:13,875
Tell me anything.

1414
01:50:14,005 --> 01:50:17,587
Tell me a good, strong lie
I can believe, but hold me.

1415
01:50:17,717 --> 01:50:20,671
Just hold me like you used to.

1416
01:50:20,803 --> 01:50:22,428
Please.

1417
01:50:37,069 --> 01:50:39,358
- No use, Lu.
- Why?

1418
01:50:39,488 --> 01:50:41,528
Because I...

1419
01:50:42,408 --> 01:50:46,655
- I don't know. I...
- Because of what? Because of her?

1420
01:50:46,787 --> 01:50:48,447
That Bible broad?

1421
01:51:06,432 --> 01:51:08,970
I'm sorry. No hard feelings.

1422
01:51:10,102 --> 01:51:13,305
- Please. Don't go yet.
- Lu, I...

1423
01:51:13,438 --> 01:51:17,815
You know, I... I could use
some of that cash after all.

1424
01:51:18,777 --> 01:51:24,897
Why, sure. Maybe I could send you some
from time to time. Till you get a job, or...

1425
01:51:25,033 --> 01:51:28,283
or maybe meet some nice
respectable man, huh?

1426
01:51:28,411 --> 01:51:31,282
I meet nice respectable men every night.

1427
01:51:36,503 --> 01:51:38,875
The best bank in America.

1428
01:51:46,012 --> 01:51:48,883
- Take care of yourself.
- Likewise, hon.

1429
01:51:52,726 --> 01:51:55,930
Class. She's got real class.

1430
01:52:11,745 --> 01:52:14,283
Wake up! Wake up, Miss Katie Jones!

1431
01:52:15,791 --> 01:52:20,833
You see before you the captain of the
SS Happiness, fishing boat extraordinary.

1432
01:52:20,963 --> 01:52:24,581
All aboard for a glorious,
carefree, happy cruise.

1433
01:52:24,717 --> 01:52:28,168
Fun, fish, frolic... and romance.

1434
01:52:28,888 --> 01:52:30,547
Guaranteed.

1435
01:52:36,312 --> 01:52:38,351
(knocking at door)

1436
01:52:39,815 --> 01:52:42,104
(knocking)

1437
01:52:42,526 --> 01:52:44,768
(persistent knocking)

1438
01:52:54,287 --> 01:53:00,041
Bill! Not one word, not one, about legal
documents, tents, moneys or lost souls.

1439
01:53:00,168 --> 01:53:03,703
We're going on a picnic, see,
and if you squeal, we'll rub you out.

1440
01:53:03,838 --> 01:53:06,080
Do you think I'd rat on a couple of pals?

1441
01:53:06,215 --> 01:53:08,588
It will be all right, won't it, for one day?

1442
01:53:08,718 --> 01:53:11,719
In that outfit, the fish'll jump
into the boat to look at you.

1443
01:53:11,846 --> 01:53:13,471
Yes.

1444
01:53:14,599 --> 01:53:17,553
We're going! We're going on a picnic!

1445
01:53:18,645 --> 01:53:21,729
I've been promising
to take her on a picnic.

1446
01:53:23,274 --> 01:53:26,228
You got that look, Bill. What's the matter?

1447
01:53:37,872 --> 01:53:41,039
Elmer the Great. Elmer the Grifter.

1448
01:53:41,167 --> 01:53:45,628
The con man conned with
the oldest badger game in the world.

1449
01:53:45,755 --> 01:53:48,376
- I don't want Shara to see these.
- She'll have to.

1450
01:53:48,508 --> 01:53:52,719
Bill, I'll do anything you say.
I'll... I'll quit. I...

1451
01:53:53,471 --> 01:53:56,009
- Don't let Shara see these.
- She's got to see them.

1452
01:53:56,349 --> 01:54:00,975
Darling, don't you think we ought
to take Bill on the picnic with us?

1453
01:54:40,766 --> 01:54:42,391
I...

1454
01:54:45,187 --> 01:54:48,722
- I suppose they're for sale?
- $25,000.

1455
01:54:51,068 --> 01:54:53,191
25,000.

1456
01:54:53,613 --> 01:54:56,982
Two o'clock today. Cash. In small bills.

1457
01:54:57,116 --> 01:55:01,410
And she wants Shara
to bring her the money, nobody else.

1458
01:55:06,500 --> 01:55:08,742
Her name is Lulu Bains.

1459
01:55:20,181 --> 01:55:22,220
Get the money.

1460
01:55:25,645 --> 01:55:29,594
One more thing. She wants you to bring
the money to 721 Lombard Street.

1461
01:55:29,732 --> 01:55:32,935
That's where she worked
before it was raided.

1462
01:55:44,538 --> 01:55:47,623
(woman) Sammy! Get out of the water!

1463
01:55:55,633 --> 01:55:57,672
(# honky-tonk piano)

1464
01:56:26,871 --> 01:56:28,864
(cat yowls)

1465
01:56:29,833 --> 01:56:32,371
Make yourself right at home, honey.

1466
01:56:53,064 --> 01:56:55,104
Be right there!

1467
01:56:55,400 --> 01:56:57,440
(cat meows)

1468
01:57:12,416 --> 01:57:14,456
(yowls)

1469
01:57:30,059 --> 01:57:32,301
I've brought the money.

1470
01:57:34,604 --> 01:57:36,846
May I have the negatives, please?

1471
01:57:52,413 --> 01:57:54,453
Extra, Jack!

1472
01:57:56,918 --> 01:58:01,746
Yeah. Yeah, I read the story,
I saw the pictures.

1473
01:58:01,881 --> 01:58:04,752
- Thank you very much.
- Did you see this?

1474
01:58:06,135 --> 01:58:08,175
I saw it.

1475
01:58:08,805 --> 01:58:11,343
- Did you see this?
- Yeah.

1476
01:58:11,474 --> 01:58:14,760
Now, I understand she brought
these pictures to you first.

1477
01:58:14,894 --> 01:58:16,768
- Yeah.
- And you turned her down?

1478
01:58:16,896 --> 01:58:18,521
Mm-hm.

1479
01:58:22,485 --> 01:58:24,110
Why?

1480
01:58:25,154 --> 01:58:29,448
These pictures prove only one thing -
that Gantry's as human as anybody else.

1481
01:58:29,576 --> 01:58:32,031
It's the obligation of a free press to print...

1482
01:58:32,161 --> 01:58:36,740
You're right, Mr. Eddington. A free press
can print anything, including lies.

1483
01:58:36,874 --> 01:58:41,501
And that's exactly what
that pornography is: blackmailing lies.

1484
01:58:43,965 --> 01:58:46,004
(# "Abide With Me")

1485
01:58:57,395 --> 01:59:00,645
Why don't those men take off their hats?

1486
01:59:25,797 --> 01:59:28,633
First time I've seen
Reverend Pengilly up there.

1487
01:59:28,759 --> 01:59:31,878
First time they've ever
been in trouble up there.

1488
01:59:37,142 --> 01:59:40,345
Thank you for coming here tonight.

1489
01:59:41,271 --> 01:59:44,605
You have every right to an explanation.

1490
01:59:45,275 --> 01:59:47,813
I will try to give it to you.

1491
01:59:48,153 --> 01:59:50,441
Tell us about sin, Sister!

1492
01:59:50,571 --> 01:59:53,821
(woman) Antichrist! You Judas, you!

1493
01:59:53,950 --> 01:59:56,156
- You false prophet!
- You faker, you!

1494
01:59:56,285 --> 01:59:58,278
- Boo!
- Yeah!

1495
01:59:58,412 --> 02:00:03,869
- Liar! Damn your own soul, Mr. Gantry!
- You call yourself a preacher?

1496
02:00:08,297 --> 02:00:10,124
Come on, Rachel.

1497
02:00:16,013 --> 02:00:18,136
Rachel, you've gotta get outta here.

1498
02:00:18,432 --> 02:00:21,932
(trumpeter plays jazz version
of "Onward Christian Soldiers")

1499
02:01:02,142 --> 02:01:04,514
Hey, Mr. Gantry!

1500
02:01:38,511 --> 02:01:40,551
(phones ringing)

1501
02:01:58,448 --> 02:02:01,069
- Hello?
- My name is Mrs. Welmer

1502
02:02:01,201 --> 02:02:03,870
I go to church every Sunday

1503
02:02:05,330 --> 02:02:07,786
You tell that Sister Sharon

1504
02:02:20,386 --> 02:02:24,715
- Get outta town, preacher woman!
- Go home, Sister!

1505
02:02:24,848 --> 02:02:26,888
- Poor Sister!
- (laughter)

1506
02:02:35,275 --> 02:02:37,600
O my God...

1507
02:02:39,153 --> 02:02:41,395
why hast thou forsaken me?

1508
02:02:46,327 --> 02:02:48,534
We'll take you home.

1509
02:03:20,820 --> 02:03:22,943
Why'd you do it?

1510
02:03:24,032 --> 02:03:26,238
Did... did she show with the money?

1511
02:03:27,327 --> 02:03:28,951
Well?

1512
02:03:30,288 --> 02:03:31,912
Yes.

1513
02:03:34,292 --> 02:03:37,459
Why didn't you go through with it? Why?

1514
02:03:39,881 --> 02:03:42,123
You wouldn't understand.

1515
02:03:50,225 --> 02:03:53,843
I know. You took
the pictures to the paper

1516
02:03:53,978 --> 02:03:56,729
cos they were gonna pay you more, huh?

1517
02:03:56,855 --> 02:03:58,931
How much did you get for 'em?

1518
02:03:59,066 --> 02:04:00,774
Nothing.

1519
02:04:00,901 --> 02:04:02,940
I didn't sell them.

1520
02:04:06,531 --> 02:04:09,201
You were never gonna sell 'em...

1521
02:04:09,326 --> 02:04:12,280
not even to that Sister woman, were you?

1522
02:04:12,412 --> 02:04:15,366
You hate Gantry that much?

1523
02:04:15,499 --> 02:04:18,120
Or do you love him that much?

1524
02:04:22,506 --> 02:04:25,127
And you're no good to me.

1525
02:04:25,259 --> 02:04:27,584
Or yourself.

1526
02:04:27,719 --> 02:04:30,175
You're no good to anybody!

1527
02:04:31,223 --> 02:04:32,717
(slap)

1528
02:04:32,933 --> 02:04:33,846
(slap)

1529
02:04:43,610 --> 02:04:46,280
Don't you know that hurts?

1530
02:06:05,941 --> 02:06:08,514
I'm sorry, Lu.

1531
02:06:08,652 --> 02:06:11,024
I'm sorry for everything.

1532
02:07:08,085 --> 02:07:10,327
Brothers and sisters...

1533
02:07:12,172 --> 02:07:13,631
goodbye.

1534
02:07:13,757 --> 02:07:14,837
Amen.

1535
02:07:17,177 --> 02:07:18,292
Jim boy!

1536
02:07:18,429 --> 02:07:21,430
You look like a man
who could use a drink.

1537
02:07:21,557 --> 02:07:27,311
Booze. You know somethin', Jim?
There oughta be a law against drinkin'.

1538
02:07:27,438 --> 02:07:30,723
- There is. Prohibition.
- That's against sellin', not drinkin'.

1539
02:07:30,858 --> 02:07:32,269
Amen.

1540
02:07:33,110 --> 02:07:35,648
- Happy days!
- I'll drink to that.

1541
02:07:37,573 --> 02:07:39,612
God, that's good.

1542
02:07:42,161 --> 02:07:44,568
Would you look at this place, Jim?

1543
02:07:47,291 --> 02:07:50,540
What were they so mad about, anyhow?

1544
02:07:50,668 --> 02:07:54,168
The mob don't like
their gods to be human.

1545
02:07:54,297 --> 02:07:57,630
- They hurt you?
- Not as much as you hurt me.

1546
02:07:57,759 --> 02:08:00,332
Nothing personal.

1547
02:08:00,470 --> 02:08:03,221
What'll you do now?

1548
02:08:03,348 --> 02:08:07,559
Well, the way I got it figured, you're up,
you're down, you sin, you're saved.

1549
02:08:07,685 --> 02:08:11,185
You do the best you can,
and you leave the rest to the Lord.

1550
02:08:11,314 --> 02:08:14,019
You really do believe
in the Lord, don't you?

1551
02:08:14,150 --> 02:08:18,942
Damn right I do. It does a man good
to get down on his knees once in a while.

1552
02:08:19,072 --> 02:08:21,479
That's why people
come to a place like this,

1553
02:08:21,616 --> 02:08:26,444
because they're scared, or sick,
or... because they got no money,

1554
02:08:26,579 --> 02:08:30,280
or too much money.
Or before a war, or after a war.

1555
02:08:32,210 --> 02:08:36,338
Praying's the cheapest
first-rate medicine I know.

1556
02:08:36,464 --> 02:08:38,920
That's why Shara was so good for them.

1557
02:08:41,552 --> 02:08:43,793
She's a lotta woman.

1558
02:08:45,973 --> 02:08:47,597
Yeah.

1559
02:08:49,059 --> 02:08:51,384
You oughta marry her.

1560
02:08:51,520 --> 02:08:56,680
- You believe in holy matrimony?
- I can recommend it, never having tried it.

1561
02:08:57,776 --> 02:09:00,148
Too late now, Jim boy.

1562
02:09:01,154 --> 02:09:03,194
Maybe not.

1563
02:09:04,116 --> 02:09:08,113
Miss Bains was waiting for me
at the paper with that story.

1564
02:09:20,215 --> 02:09:23,133
- How'd you get her to do it?
- I didn't.

1565
02:09:25,637 --> 02:09:28,508
The Lord sure moves in mysterious ways.

1566
02:09:35,606 --> 02:09:40,149
Any minute now, you will hear
the voice of Sister Sharon Falconer,

1567
02:09:40,277 --> 02:09:42,685
but not that, I'm afraid, of Elmer Gantry.

1568
02:09:43,030 --> 02:09:46,564
For Mr. Gantry has completely vanished
since three nights ago.

1569
02:09:46,700 --> 02:09:49,950
I've checked the police,
hospitals, railroads, bus depots...

1570
02:09:50,078 --> 02:09:51,621
Where is he? Where?

1571
02:09:51,747 --> 02:09:56,872
Every wire service in the country's asking
the same question. He's page-one news.

1572
02:09:57,002 --> 02:10:00,086
If anything happened to him,
you'd know it.

1573
02:10:04,551 --> 02:10:06,176
Yes.

1574
02:10:07,304 --> 02:10:09,546
Yes, I would know it.

1575
02:10:11,934 --> 02:10:16,062
He'll be here, I'm... I'm sure of it.
We'll wait for him.

1576
02:10:16,188 --> 02:10:21,691
We can't wait. Some of those people
have been out there since early morning.

1577
02:10:21,817 --> 02:10:25,317
- I won't go on without him.
- Maybe he won't be back.

1578
02:10:27,823 --> 02:10:29,862
Just a feeling.

1579
02:10:34,246 --> 02:10:36,203
We'll wait for him.

1580
02:10:41,836 --> 02:10:44,921
(congregation sings
"Onward Christian Soldiers")

1581
02:11:08,697 --> 02:11:10,321
Elmer?

1582
02:11:16,496 --> 02:11:18,240
Oh, darling!

1583
02:11:18,373 --> 02:11:20,116
Darling!

1584
02:11:21,960 --> 02:11:23,787
- Gantry's back.
- How do you know?

1585
02:11:23,920 --> 02:11:27,621
Somebody just saw him.
Where's a phone around here?

1586
02:11:28,300 --> 02:11:32,167
- What about your friend Gantry?
- Quite a guy! Son of a...

1587
02:11:32,304 --> 02:11:34,545
(band plays fanfare)

1588
02:11:36,641 --> 02:11:38,930
Let me look at you.

1589
02:11:39,060 --> 02:11:42,061
Three endless days without a word.

1590
02:11:42,188 --> 02:11:43,932
Why?

1591
02:11:44,065 --> 02:11:47,600
Don't you realise how much I need you?

1592
02:11:50,405 --> 02:11:53,239
Are you angry? With me?

1593
02:11:53,365 --> 02:11:56,651
- No, Shara.
- Don't ever leave me again. Ever.

1594
02:11:58,370 --> 02:12:00,328
Shara.

1595
02:12:00,456 --> 02:12:02,080
Yes?

1596
02:12:03,334 --> 02:12:05,706
What would happen if we chucked it all,

1597
02:12:05,836 --> 02:12:10,000
beat it across the state line,
get good and married, like most folks?

1598
02:12:10,132 --> 02:12:14,461
Have a bunch of kids, take 'em
to a ball game like most folks.

1599
02:12:14,595 --> 02:12:19,636
Go dancin'. We've never gone
dancin' together, not even once.

1600
02:12:19,767 --> 02:12:22,222
Let's do it, Shara. Tonight. Right now.

1601
02:12:22,353 --> 02:12:25,852
- But all those people...
- If they wanna pray...

1602
